<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3718] Regular-Expression-Evaluates-Null-As-True</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3718</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Issue reported groovy-user forum: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Regular-Expression-Evaluates-Null-As-True--to25223536.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Regular-Expression-Evaluates-Null-As-True--to25223536.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/ * Returns true */&lt;br/&gt;
println null ==~ /&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;^0-9&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;+/ &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/ * Returns false */&lt;br/&gt;
println null ==~ /&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0-9&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;+/&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In both the cases, it should probably just throw NPE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
